Name: Denmark 10-year Government Bond Yield (with GFD extension)
Periodicity:
Monthly From Sep 1788 To Dec 1981
Daily From Jan 1982 To Nov 2021
Metadata:
Sources: London Times (1821-1844), Banker`s Magazine and The Economist (1845-1858), Statistiske Department, Statistisk Arbog, Copenhagen: Statistiske Dept. (1864-31), League of Nations (1932-45), Danmarks Bank, Monetary Review (1946-)
Notes: The Denmark 4% Crown Bonds (Kroondeenen) (Amsterdam SE) (BGDNK4K-AM) is used from September 1788 to August 1825, the Denmark 3% Stock of 1825 (BGDNK3S-LO) is used from September 1825 to December 1869, the Denmark 4% Stock of 1862 (BGDNK462-LO) is used from January 1870 to November 1886, both trading in London. Domestic quotes begin with the Denmark 3.50% Consolidated Bond (BGDNK35C-KO) which is used from December 1886 to November 1937, and the Denmark 4.50% Gold Trust Receipts due 1962 (BGDNK4562) which traded in New York is used from December 1938 to September 1958. In Denmark, the consolidated 3.5% bond is used through 1976. In 1977, the 10-year bond is used. Denmark has not defaulted on its bonds.
